{"type":"message","id":"f0d74a94","parentId":"bd919205","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:16:48.642Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iiaqeyxvku9g_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5604\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2311\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.py\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.py\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 091617 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority - it tests the key insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I need to start by creating a classifier that can identify invariants vs variants across the existing pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"rapid-harbor","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5604\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2311\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.py\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.py\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 091617 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority - it tests the key insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I need to start by creating a classifier that can identify invariants vs variants across the existing pulse logs.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358208641}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae65870f","parentId":"f0d74a94","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:16:48.645Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iiaqeyxvku9g_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 091318\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most effective single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the immediate priority is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression) which is the next step for Phase 1 advancement. The pending actions include:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION specifically is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSo I should implement the TIC classifier. Let me first look at what pulse logs exist to understand the data structure.\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse log is: `pulse_2026-03-24 091117.md`\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. First examine existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n3. Run it against the logs\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for the TIC classifier that will:\r\n1. Load pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features (content patterns, actions, goals)\r\n3. Classify invariant vs variant elements\r\n4. Attempt to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 advancement directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. Need to examine existing pulse logs to understand their structure before implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine recent pulse logs to understand structure, then create TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPATTERNS = {\r\n    \"goal_refs\": r\"(Phase \\d+|Goal|Action|NEXT)\",\r\n    \"file_ops\": r\"`([^`]+)`\",  # backtick-quoted paths\r\n    \"actions\": r\"### (OBSERVATION|ACTION|MUTATION)\",  # section headers\r\n    \"decay_refs\": r\"(λ|decay|gap|compress|invariant)\",  # decay/memory terms\r\n}\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract feature vector for invariance analysis.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {}\r\n    for name, pattern in PATTERNS.items():\r\n        matches = re.findall(pattern, text)\r\n        features[name] = {\r\n            \"count\": len(matches),\r\n            \"items\": matches,\r\n            \"bigrams\": list(zip(matches[:-1], matches[1:])) if len(matches) > 1 else []\r\n        }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(features_current, features_previous):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify features as INVARIANT (persistent) or VARIANT (ephemeral).\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    variants = []\r\n    \r\n    for feat_name in features_current:\r\n        curr = features_current[feat_name][\"count\"]\r\n        prev = features_previous.get(feat_name, {}).get(\"count\", 0)\r\n        \r\n        if curr > 0 and prev > 0:\r\n            invariants.append(feat_name)\r\n        elif curr > 0 and prev == 0:\r\n            variants.append(feat_name)\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(features_invariant):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    predictions = []\r\n    for inv in features_invariant:\r\n        predictions.append(f\"CONTINUE_{inv}\")\r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulse_log(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Full analysis of a single pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    return extract_features(content)\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    if len(logs) < 3:\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Need at least 3 pulse logs\", \"found\": len(logs)}\r\n    \r\n    results = {\r\n        \"total_pulses\": len(logs),\r\n        \"classification_accuracy\": 0,\r\n        \"prediction_accuracy\": 0,\r\n        \"invariants_found\": [],\r\n        \"variants_found\": [],\r\n        \"details\": []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    all_features = []\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        features = analyze_pulse_log(log)\r\n        all_features.append((log.name, features))\r\n    \r\n    # Classify invariants across all pulses\r\n    invariant_counts = Counter()\r\n    for name, features in all_features:\r\n        for feat_name, feat_data in features.items():\r\n            if feat_data[\"count\"] > 0:\r\n                invariant_counts[feat_name] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Feature invariant if present in >70% of pulses\r\n    threshold = 0.7 * len(logs)\r\n    for feat, count in invariant_counts.items():\r\n        if count >= threshold:\r\n            results[\"invariants_found\"].append(feat)\r\n        else:\r\n            results[\"variants_found\"].append(feat)\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate classification accuracy (invariants vs variants)\r\n    n_invariant = len(results[\"invariants_found\"])\r\n    n_total = len(invariant_counts)\r\n    results[\"classification_accuracy\"] = n_invariant / n_total if n_total > 0 else 0\r\n    \r\n    # Simple next-pulse prediction: if invariant, predict it continues\r\n    # Success = invariant features appear in next pulse\r\n    correct_predictions = 0\r\n    total_predictions = 0\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(all_features)\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:13:56\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358208642}}
