{"type":"message","id":"1bb5b8b2","parentId":"5442e9b9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:17:05.762Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d37aephiebhw_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 091617\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action I should take to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Key insight from this session: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n- Next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Pending actions include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next action based on the notes is the TIC experiment:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to look at the existing pulse logs to understand the structure and implement the TIC classifier. Let me check what logs exist and their format.\r\n\r\nLooking at recent: Last pulse is `pulse_2026-03-24 091318.md` - so there should be several pulse logs in the logs/ directory.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Read the pulse logs\r\n2. Implement a classifier that identifies invariants (patterns that persist across pulses) vs variants (unique to specific pulses)\r\n3. Test prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create a script or document that starts the TIC experiment implementation. I could:\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment script\r\n2. Create a research document outlining the experiment design\r\n3. Analyze the pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's a `logs` directory and what format the pulse logs are in. Since I don't have filesystem access in this moment, I should create the experiment framework that assumes the logs exist.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a Python script to systematically analyze pulse logs, identifying temporal invariants and variants. The script will implement a classification mechanism to track persistent and unique patterns across different pulse logs.\r\n\r\nThe core strategy involves developing a `tic_classifier.py` that can:\r\n- Parse log contents\r\n- Extract distinguishing features\r\n- Classify elements as invariant or variant\r\n- Provide a framework for predicting subsequent pulse contents\r\n\r\nBy starting with this script, I'm laying the groundwork for a comprehensive temporal invariance compression experiment that will help validate the proposed theoretical approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority - it tests the key insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. I need to start by creating a classifier that can identify invariants vs variants across the existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that reads pulse logs, extracts temporal patterns, classifies them as invariant or variant, and attempts to predict subsequent pulse content. This implements the core TIC experiment framework.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"# Goals:\",           # Goal structure persists\r\n    r\"## Active\",          # Active tasks always present\r\n    r\"## Pending\",         # Pending section exists\r\n    r\"### OBSERVATION\",    # Observation header\r\n    r\"### ACTION\",         # Action header\r\n    r\"Phase \\d\",           # Phase markers\r\n]\r\n\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # Dates (change per pulse)\r\n    r\"Last updated:.*\",    # Update timestamps\r\n    r\"Last pulse:.*\",      # Current pulse reference\r\n    r\"pulse_\\d{8}_\\d{6}\", # Specific pulse IDs\r\n]\r\n\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse log files sorted by date.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        logs.append(f.read_text())\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_sections(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Split pulse log into structural sections.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    parts = re.split(r\"(###\\s+\\w+)\", text)\r\n    current = \"header\"\r\n    for part in parts:\r\n        if re.match(r\"###\\s+\\w+\", part):\r\n            current = part.strip(\"# \").strip().lower()\r\n            sections[current] = \"\"\r\n        else:\r\n            sections[current] = (sections.get(current) or \"\") + part\r\n    return sections\r\n\r\n\r\ndef classify_line(line):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a line as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, line):\r\n            return \"invariant\"\r\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, line):\r\n            return \"variant\"\r\n    return \"neutral\"\r\n\r\n\r\ndef analyze_invariants(logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Find patterns that persist across all/most pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    line_freq = Counter()\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        for line in log.split(\"\\n\"):\r\n            stripped = line.strip()\r\n            if stripped:\r\n                line_freq[stripped] += 1\r\n    \r\n    invariants = {line for line, count in line_freq.items() \r\n                  if count >= len(logs) * 0.7}  # Appears in 70%+ of pulses\r\n    variants =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:16:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358225758}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac42b673","parentId":"1bb5b8b2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:17:11.038Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran and created a proposed mutation for `tic/tic_classifier.py`. Let me check if the file was actually created and read the mutation file to understand what was proposed.","thinkingSignature":"1bf3f55f4c44afb517b6d972cc5e4806668045fcbf4ef5b23cb1b16a69506ece"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rh77d5bnpkw0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 091617.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4041,"output":91,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16269,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774358225763}}
{"type":"message","id":"be9ac52f","parentId":"ac42b673","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:17:11.045Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rh77d5bnpkw0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿tic/tic_classifier.py\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"# Goals:\",           # Goal structure persists\n    r\"## Active\",          # Active tasks always present\n    r\"## Pending\",         # Pending section exists\n    r\"### OBSERVATION\",    # Observation header\n    r\"### ACTION\",         # Action header\n    r\"Phase \\d\",           # Phase markers\n]\n\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # Dates (change per pulse)\n    r\"Last updated:.*\",    # Update timestamps\n    r\"Last pulse:.*\",      # Current pulse reference\n    r\"pulse_\\d{8}_\\d{6}\", # Specific pulse IDs\n]\n\n\ndef load_pulse_logs():\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse log files sorted by date.\"\"\"\n    logs = []\n    for f in sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\n        logs.append(f.read_text())\n    return logs\n\n\ndef extract_sections(text):\n    \"\"\"Split pulse log into structural sections.\"\"\"\n    sections = {}\n    parts = re.split(r\"(###\\s+\\w+)\", text)\n    current = \"header\"\n    for part in parts:\n        if re.match(r\"###\\s+\\w+\", part):\n            current = part.strip(\"# \").strip().lower()\n            sections[current] = \"\"\n        else:\n            sections[current] = (sections.get(current) or \"\") + part\n    return sections\n\n\ndef classify_line(line):\n    \"\"\"Classify a line as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\n        if re.search(pattern, line):\n            return \"invariant\"\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\n        if re.search(pattern, line):\n            return \"variant\"\n    return \"neutral\"\n\n\ndef analyze_invariants(logs):\n    \"\"\"Find patterns that persist across all/most pulses.\"\"\"\n    line_freq = Counter()\n    for log in logs:\n        for line in log.split(\"\\n\"):\n            stripped = line.strip()\n            if stripped:\n                line_freq[stripped] += 1\n    \n    invariants = {line for line, count in line_freq.items() \n                  if count >= len(logs) * 0.7}  # Appears in 70%+ of pulses\n    variants =\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358231043}}
